    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 66 species in six families worldwide, including cormorants, boobies, gannets, tropic birds, and frigate birds. They are water birds with all four toes webbed and a bill that is hooked or straight and sharply pointed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
